main event: A ground-visual observation of an unidentified object near the Salton Sea in California on March 15, 1955.
interesting points: The weather conditions were overcast and calm.
The report notes that the object could have been a balloon, but there was insufficient data to make a conclusive determination.
There were no photographs taken of the object.
No military personnel were involved in the observation.
location: 40 m S of Salton Sea, Cal.
